>How do these boards stack up, and is there any particular Intel chip
>versions I should be specifically looking for or avoiding? The
>computer will be doing a lot of 3D CAD/CAM for Electrical Engineering
>and (of course) games...

Avoid anything without PB Cache. This gives you the most performance
boost. More than anything else. If you get PB cache, there is really
no need for EDO RAM. performance difference is only about 2-3%.

Check out the Tyan Titan III motherboard. It's probably the best
implimentation of the Triton chipset on the market. With a 100Mhz it's
slightly slower than DELL, or Acers P133's. Even with Fast-Page RAM
(regular).




