Actually the pipeline cache results in major performance increase, about 15%,
not the EDO RAM which is minimal. If you are looking for expandability to
200Mhz, the Micronics, and Acer won't do it, and with the Endeavor by Intel you
must pay extra for their sound card. That leaves Asus from your list. There are
also excellent boards by Supermicro and Tyan that are high performance and
reasonable. The Micronics is NOT reasonably priced.
